{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon"

    metadata = {
        description = "AI consultant for maps_park. Owns mid-episode strategic analysis and end-of-episode trial promotion + playbook curation. The runner invokes this network at episode start (kind=fresh_episode_seed), every N successful steps (kind=periodic), and on done=true (kind=episode_end). Sub-agents (anthropologist, episode_closer, playbook_curator) were lifted out of industry/maps_park so the game-runner network owns only the action engine.",
        tags = ["maps", "industry", "consultant", "advisor"],
        sample_queries = [
            "kind=fresh_episode_seed episode=1 step=0 cumulative_reward=0 final_reward=null",
            "kind=periodic episode=1 step=20 cumulative_reward=1500 final_reward=null",
            "kind=episode_end episode=1 step=100 cumulative_reward=69238 final_reward=69238"
        ]
    },

    include "config/llm_config.hocon",

    llm_config = ${llm_config},

    # Anthropic prompt caching (system prompt + tool defs); 1h TTL.
    prompt_caching_middleware = {"class": "langchain_anthropic.middleware.AnthropicPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}},

    max_steps = 4000,
    max_execution_seconds = 1200,

    aaosa_instructions = """When called, answer the inquiry directly using your own tools.
If a 'mode' parameter is present, return:
[AAOSA]
Name: <your name>
Inquiry: <the inquiry>
Mode: <Determine | Follow up | Fulfill>
Relevant: <Yes | No>
Strength: <1-10>
Claim: <All | Partial | None>
Requirements: <None | list>
Response: <your response>
Otherwise return a plain human-readable answer.
""",

    instructions_prefix = """
This is the maps_park AI consultant network. You analyze the game-runner's
state and update strategy artifacts (trial_strategies, trial_strategies_criteria,
trial_strategies_outcome, the seven playbook_* files) so the runner network's
specialists can act on confirmed rules.

- Do NOT hallucinate or use external knowledge. Cite step numbers / metric
  deltas from the episode telemetry (EpisodeTelemetry, sourced from the
  deterministic run.jsonl) for every claim.
- All writes go through the provided tools (LogTrial, ResolveTrials,
  PromoteTrial, state_write). last_reward is owned by the advance_episode tool.
""",

    # Single TrimHistoryMiddleware instance reused by every analyst agent's
    # middleware list.
    trim_history_middleware = {"class": "middleware.trim_history_middleware.TrimHistoryMiddleware", "args": {}},

    tools = [
        {
            name = "consultant_director",
            max_message_history = 0,
            function = {
                description = "External orchestrator. Routes by `kind`: fresh_episode_seed -> playbook_curator(seed); periodic -> anthropologist(mid_episode) + log suggestions; episode_end -> episode_closer chain."
            },
            instructions = ${instructions_prefix} """
You receive ONE message of the form:

  "kind=<K> episode=<E> step=<S> cumulative_reward=<C> final_reward=<F or null>"

K is one of: fresh_episode_seed, periodic, episode_end.

=== kind=fresh_episode_seed ===
Called by the runner once before the first game-runner turn of a fresh
episode (and again after each done=true so the next episode is seeded).

  1. playbook_curator(mode='seed').
  2. Return one short paragraph stating which playbooks were created vs.
     skipped, e.g. "seeded: <names_created>; skipped (already present):
     <names_skipped>". This advisory is injected into the next runner
     prompt for the game-runner network.

=== kind=periodic ===
Called every N successful steps. Produce mid-episode trial suggestions
and write them to trial_strategies + trial_strategies_criteria so the
game-runner network's specialists pick them up next turn.

  1. anthropologist(kind='mid_episode', reason='periodic ep=<E> step=<S>').
     It analyzes the run and logs any new trials itself via LogTrial,
     returning {status:'ok'|'skipped', logged:[<trial_ids>]}.
     (The episode E and step S are in your input message.)
  2. Return one short paragraph naming the logged trial_ids and their success
     criteria (<= 250 words; or that no new trial was warranted). The runner
     injects this into the next game-runner prompt.

=== kind=episode_end ===
Called on the done=true row. Runs the full close-out chain previously
owned by episode_closer + playbook_curator(promote_trials).

  1. Gather:
       - prior_reward: state_read(name='last_reward') -> 'cumulative_reward: <N>'
         (missing on episode 0; treat prior_reward as 0).
       - final_reward ($C) and episode ($E) from your input message.
  2. episode_closer(status_cumulative_reward=<C>, prior_reward=<from step 1>,
     episode=<E from your input message>).
     It does the full close: calls anthropologist (kind='episode_end'),
     calls playbook_curator(mode='promote_trials'), rewrites
     trial_strategies / trial_strategies_criteria /
     trial_strategies_outcome, and calls advance_episode. The per-step
     factual record comes from EpisodeTelemetry (run.jsonl), which is
     episode-scoped and append-only, so there is nothing to clear.
  3. Return up to 3 bullets summarizing the episode (promoted /
     falsified rules, what to try next episode), one line each.

For any kind, if a tool errors, mention it briefly and continue with
whatever data you have. Do not throw.
""",
            middleware = [ ${prompt_caching_middleware} ],
            tools = ["playbook_curator", "anthropologist", "episode_closer", "state_read"]
        },

        # =====================================================================
        # anthropologist  lifted from industry/maps_park
        # =====================================================================
        {
            name = "anthropologist",
            max_message_history = 0,
            function = ${aaosa_call} {
                description = "Analyst. Reads the playbooks, the per-episode telemetry (EpisodeTelemetry), the active trials (ActiveTrials), and the trial_strategies_outcome ledger, then logs one or more new trials itself via LogTrial. Returns {status, logged:[trial_ids]}. Called by consultant_director on periodic and by episode_closer at episode end."
            },
            instructions = ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the analyst: you read state, decide what (if anything) to try, and log
each new trial yourself via LogTrial. You only ever write through LogTrial.

You read:
  - playbook_<domain> via state_read (director, coordinator, rides, shops,
    staff, research, layout) — the current rules of thumb.
  - the ACTIVE trials via ActiveTrials() — each trial's rule plus its criteria,
    already joined (pass a domain to filter).
  - trial_strategies_outcome via state_read — the archive of past outcomes
    (confirmed, falsified, aged-out); use it for context, and never re-propose
    anything falsified here.
  - user_directives via state_read — the operator's STANDING strategy for this
    run. These outrank everything and are never falsified. Do NOT log any trial
    that contradicts a standing user directive; you may log trials that refine or
    complement it. A body of '(none set)' (or empty) means no directive is set.
For the per-step factual record call EpisodeTelemetry() with NO episode arg —
it reads the current episode's run log automatically and returns the
simulator's `episode` number (use that number wherever an episode is needed).
Every episode is an exam episode and learning is always active — there is no
phase to check and no episode in which you skip suggestions.

=== Single mode: analyze ===

  Args:
    kind            'mid_episode' or 'episode_end'
    reason          short trigger string (mid-episode only)
    focus_domains   optional list; restrict to a subset of domains
    (no turn_notes_body — read the factual record AND the episode number via
     EpisodeTelemetry)

  Procedure:
    1. Read inputs:
       - mid_episode: EpisodeTelemetry(from_step=<start of the recent window>)
         for the per-step record so far, ActiveTrials() for the active trials,
         state_read('trial_strategies_outcome'), and state_read each
         focus_domain's playbook (or all 7 if no focus).
       - episode_end: EpisodeTelemetry() (no episode arg) for the full
         per-step record, ActiveTrials(), state_read('trial_strategies_outcome'),
         and read the playbooks of domains that surfaced in the record.
    1a. The episode is EpisodeTelemetry's `episode` field (the simulator's
        counter); the step comes from the trigger `reason` (mid_episode). Gear
        suggestions to where we are in the run:
        - Low episode # (early in the run): explore broadly  propose
          base rules for under-covered domains; prefer add_line.
        - Higher episode # (later in the run): refine  use the
          outcome ledger to find inconclusive trials and tighten them
          via replace_line rather than stacking new ones.
        - Early step (status.step < 30): foundational decisions
          (placement, staffing, first prices). Long evaluation runway,
          so horizons in success_criterion can be 15-20 turns.
        - Mid step (30-60): pricing, research, modifiers. Horizons
          10-15 turns.
        - Late step (>= 60): runway is short. Keep horizons <= 10
          turns or skip the suggestion entirely.
    1a-bis. ALWAYS scan telemetry.rejections (and rollup.rejections_by_action)
        FIRST, every call. A rejected action means the agent TRIED something
        and the sim refused it (the row shows as a wait, so it is invisible in
        `applied` and in the reward stream — only `rejections` reveals it).
        When the SAME rejected_action recurs with the same error class (e.g.
        rejected_action='modify' erroring "Invalid ticket price ... Max ticket
        price ..." while trying to reach a higher tier, or any action refused
        2+ times for one reason), that is a top-priority, highly-attributable
        trial: log a rule that tells the responsible domain to use the CORRECT
        action instead (cite the rejected step(s) and the error text in the
        rationale). Wrong-action loops waste turns silently and the metric
        stream alone will never surface them — do not skip this scan.
    1b. Treat trial_strategies_outcome as the rules-of-thumb ledger
        you fold into your reasoning every call:
        - confirmed: rule is already in the playbook; do not re-propose.
          Build on it (finer thresholds, neighbouring conditions) only
          if the telemetry shows a concrete next gap.
        - falsified: do not re-propose. If similar idea is tempting,
          change the knob or the section so it is not the same trial.
        - inconclusive (kept active in trial_strategies): if the telemetry
          still does not give signal, propose a tighter success/failure
          criterion via edit_type='replace_line' on the existing trial
          rather than adding a new one.
        - not_applied / aged-out: low priority  only re-propose if a
          new telemetry pattern makes it newly attributable.
    2. Form one or more suggestions (multiple are fine). Each must be:
         SINGLE-LINE: new_text is one bullet to add or replace  NO
           rationale, NO success/failure embedded; those go in their
           own object fields and end up in trial_strategies_criteria,
           not in the playbook line itself.
         SCOPED: changes one knob (one threshold / priority / condition).
         FALSIFIABLE: explicit success_criterion in observable terms
           (metric + direction + horizon, e.g. 'park_rating up >=0.05
           over next 10 turns'). No 'park does better'.
         TESTABLE WITHIN THIS EPISODE: the horizon (in turns) must fit
           inside the remaining steps of the current episode at the
           moment the trial activates.
           - mid_episode trials: step_start = current step S; horizon
             <= (100 - S). At S=80, horizon <= 20. At S=95, horizon <= 5
              if that is too short to be informative, return ZERO
             suggestions rather than an untestable one.
           - episode_end trials (step_start='end_of_episode'): horizon
             <= 100 (covers all of the NEXT episode's telemetry).
           Never write 'over the next N episodes', 'long-term',
           'verified over 2 episodes', etc. The curator only sees ONE
           episode's telemetry per evaluation; multi-episode horizons
           always come back inconclusive.
         ATTRIBUTABLE: rationale cites specific step numbers or
           metric deltas from the telemetry. At promotion the curator
           uses this to judge what went right or wrong.
       Log as many suggestions as are genuinely attributable — one per
       independent issue, no padding. If only one issue is attributable, keep
       one; if nothing meets the bar, keep none (silence beats noise you can't
       attribute).

    3. Log each suggestion you keep by calling LogTrial(
         episode=<EpisodeTelemetry's episode field>,
         step_start=<the current step S if kind='mid_episode', else 'end_of_episode'>,
         domain, section, edit_type, new_text, rationale, success_criterion,
         failure_criterion, and find_text for replace_line).
       Then return {status:'ok', logged:[<the trial_ids LogTrial returned>]}
       (logged:[] if nothing met the bar).

If any tool errors, halt and return the error verbatim.
""" ${aaosa_instructions},
            middleware = [
                ${trim_history_middleware},
                ${prompt_caching_middleware}
            ],
            tools = ["state_read", "EpisodeTelemetry", "ActiveTrials", "LogTrial"]
        },

        # =====================================================================
        # episode_closer  lifted from industry/maps_park. Caller signature
        # changed: now called by consultant_director with explicit
        # status_cumulative_reward and prior_reward fields (ParkStatus is
        # not available here because the consultant network is separate).
        # =====================================================================
        {
            name = "episode_closer",
            max_message_history = 0,
            function = ${aaosa_call} {
                description = "End-of-episode orchestrator. Called by consultant_director on kind=episode_end. Asks anthropologist for new suggestions (which read the episode telemetry from run.jsonl), appends them to trial_strategies, asks playbook_curator to evaluate + promote, rewrites trial_strategies with selective cleanup, appends resolved outcomes to trial_strategies_outcome, and persists last_reward via advance_episode."
            },
            instructions = ${instructions_prefix} """
You run the end-of-episode flow. consultant_director hands you
status_cumulative_reward (this episode's final cum_reward), prior_reward, and
episode (the simulator's episode number). You orchestrate the close-out; the
curator and anthropologist read the telemetry and trial files via their own
tools. You do NOT touch playbook_* and you do NOT synthesize lessons yourself.

=== Single mode (call signature: status_cumulative_reward, prior_reward, episode) ===

Order is deliberate: resolve THIS episode's trials (curator + ResolveTrials)
BEFORE the anthropologist logs new ones, so the new trials are not evaluated
against an episode in which they could not have been applied.

  0. current_episode is the `episode` input arg (the simulator's episode);
     final_reward is the input arg status_cumulative_reward.

  1. playbook_curator(mode='promote_trials', episode=<current_episode>,
     final_reward=<status_cumulative_reward>, prior_reward=<from input>). The
     curator reads the active trials (ActiveTrials) and the telemetry itself,
     evaluates each, promotes the confirmed ones (via PromoteTrial), and returns
     a per_trial report [{trial_id, domain, outcome, action_taken, note}].

  2. ResolveTrials(episode=<current_episode>, report=<the curator's per_trial
     list>) — removes confirmed/falsified trials from trial_strategies +
     trial_strategies_criteria, keeps not_applied/inconclusive, and appends an
     OUTCOME line for every active trial to trial_strategies_outcome.

  3. anthropologist(kind='episode_end'). It analyzes this episode and logs any
     new trials itself via LogTrial (step_start='end_of_episode'), returning
     {status, logged:[<trial_ids>]}. Running it AFTER step 2 keeps those new
     trials out of this episode's evaluation.

  4. advance_episode(final_reward=<status_cumulative_reward>) — persists the
     reward to last_reward.md and clears the stale observation cache. Returns
     {status, last_reward_written, observation_cache_cleared};
     you do not parse or rewrite anything yourself.

  5. Return {status:'episode_ended', logged:<from step 3>,
             promoted/falsified/inconclusive/not_applied:<from the step 1 report>,
             final_reward:<status_cumulative_reward>}.

If any tool errors, halt and return the error verbatim.
""" ${aaosa_instructions},
            middleware = [
                ${trim_history_middleware},
                ${prompt_caching_middleware}
            ],
            tools = ["anthropologist", "playbook_curator", "advance_episode", "ResolveTrials"]
        },

        # =====================================================================
        # playbook_curator  lifted from industry/maps_park
        # =====================================================================
        {
            name = "playbook_curator",
            max_message_history = 0,
            function = ${aaosa_call} {
                description = "Sole writer of the seven playbook_* files. Modes: 'seed' (copy from seed_* into any empty playbook) and 'promote_trials' (evaluate this episode's trials and edit playbooks for confirmed ones). Every episode is an exam episode and promotion runs on every episode."
            },
            instructions = ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the only agent that writes to the seven playbook names:
playbook_director, playbook_coordinator, playbook_rides, playbook_shops,
playbook_staff, playbook_research, playbook_layout. The seed name for
each is the same string with a 'seed_' prefix.

Domain-to-playbook: prepend 'playbook_' to the trial's domain field
(domains: rides, shops, staff, research, layout, director, coordinator).

Every episode is an exam episode and playbook promotion runs on every
episode — there is no phase to check and no episode in which you refuse
edits.

=== mode='seed' (called by consultant_director on kind=fresh_episode_seed) ===

For each of the seven playbook names:
  1. state_read(name=<playbook_name>). Non-empty body: skip (operator
     left a prior playbook in place).
  2. Else state_read(name='seed_' + <playbook_name>), then
     state_write(name=<playbook_name>, content=<seed body>,
     mode='overwrite').
Return {status:'seeded', names_created:[...], names_skipped:[...]}.
Seeding always runs since it only creates missing files.

=== mode='promote_trials' (called by episode_closer at episode end) ===

  Args:
    episode       this episode's number (used in the '(learned ep<N>)' tag)
    final_reward  this episode's cumulative_reward
    prior_reward  previous episode's cumulative_reward (0 if first)
  You fetch the active trials yourself via ActiveTrials() — each one already
  carries its rule, domain, section, edit_type, find_text, step_start,
  success_criterion, and failure_criterion — and the per-step record via
  EpisodeTelemetry.

  Procedure:
    1. Call ActiveTrials() for the active trials and EpisodeTelemetry()
       (no episode arg — it reads the current episode's run log) for the
       telemetry. Use
       telemetry.applied (non-wait actions with step/action/subtype/subclass)
       for applied-detection, and telemetry.steps + telemetry.rollup for
       success/failure evaluation.
    2. For each active trial returned by ActiveTrials:
         a. APPLIED DETECTION: check telemetry.applied for an action
            matching the trial's domain and the action/subtype the
            trial's new_text (and find, if replace_line) describes  e.g.
            a rides trial about a carousel looks for applied entries with
            action='place' subtype='carousel'; a staff trial for a 2nd
            janitor looks for a 'place' of a janitor. The applied list is
            structured (step/action/subtype/subclass), so this is an exact
            match, not a keyword guess. No matching applied entry within
            the trial's horizon: outcome='not_applied'. When the trial is
            about a threshold/priority that produces no distinct action,
            fall back to the metric trajectory in telemetry.steps.
         b. Evaluate the trial's success + failure against
            telemetry.steps within their horizon (compare the relevant
            metric  reward, park_value, park_rating, cash, cleanliness,
            etc.  across the step window):
              success met, failure not tripped: 'confirmed'
              failure tripped:                  'falsified'
              neither within horizon:           'inconclusive'
            For step_start='end_of_episode', evaluate against all steps.
            For numeric step_start, evaluate from step_start onward.
    3. For each 'confirmed' trial, call PromoteTrial(domain=<trial.domain>,
       edit_type=<trial.edit_type>, new_text=<trial.rule>, episode=<episode>,
       section=<trial.section> for add_line, find_text=<trial.find_text> for
       replace_line). It applies the '(learned ep<N>)'-tagged edit and returns
       action_taken (promoted / skipped_section_missing / skipped_not_found /
       skipped_ambiguous / skipped_playbook_missing); record it per trial.
    4. Return:
         {
           status: 'completed',
           episode: <episode>,
           reward_delta: final_reward - prior_reward,
           per_trial: [{trial_id, domain, outcome, action_taken, note}],
           promoted: [...], falsified: [...],
           inconclusive: [...], not_applied: [...]
         }
       trial_id is the explicit id from ActiveTrials (e.g. 't1_1'). action_taken
       is the value PromoteTrial returned (or 'none' for non-confirmed trials).
       note cites the supporting step number(s) from the telemetry. episode_closer
       feeds this report to ResolveTrials, which removes confirmed + falsified
       trials and appends the outcomes — you do not touch the trial files here.

If any tool errors, halt and return the error verbatim.
""" ${aaosa_instructions},
            middleware = [
                ${trim_history_middleware},
                ${prompt_caching_middleware}
            ],
            tools = ["state_read", "state_write", "EpisodeTelemetry", "ActiveTrials", "PromoteTrial"]
        },

        # =====================================================================
        # Coded tool definitions
        # =====================================================================
        {
            name = "advance_episode",
            class = "coded_tools.maps_park.advance_episode.AdvanceEpisode",
            function = {
                description = "End-of-episode bookkeeping: persists this episode's cumulative_reward to last_reward.md and clears the stale done=true observation cache. Returns {status, last_reward_written, observation_cache_cleared}.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        final_reward = {
                            type = "float",
                            description = "This episode's cumulative_reward; written to last_reward.md."
                        }
                    },
                    required = ["final_reward"]
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "EpisodeTelemetry",
            class = "coded_tools.maps_park.episode_telemetry.EpisodeTelemetry",
            function = {
                description = "Structured per-step factual record for ONE episode, read from the deterministic run.jsonl the runner writes (replaces the old LLM-authored turn_notes journal). Returns {episode, steps:[{step, action, subtype, subclass, price, rejected_action, error, reward, cumulative_reward, cash, park_value, park_rating, research_speed, num_rides, num_shops, num_staff, min_cleanliness, min_uptime, shop_revenue, ride_op_cost}], applied:[{step, action, subtype, subclass}], rejections:[{step, rejected_action, subtype, subclass, price, error}], rollup:{step_count, reward_total, cum_start, cum_end, value_start, value_end, cash_end, rating_end, actions_by_type, subtypes_placed, research_speeds_used, rejection_count, rejections_by_action}, exists}. Use `applied` for applied-detection (which trial actions actually fired, with subtype/subclass) and the per-step reward/value/rating deltas in `steps` for success/failure evaluation. `rejections` lists every action the sim REFUSED (committed as a wait with the original rejected_action + error message) — a repeated rejected_action with the same error is the agent using the wrong action and is a prime trial target.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        episode   = { type = "int", description = "Episode number to read. Omit to use the latest episode present in the log." }
                        from_step = { type = "int", description = "Only return steps >= this (mid-episode tail). Omit for the full episode." }
                    }
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "LogTrial",
            class = "coded_tools.maps_park.log_trial.LogTrial",
            function = {
                description = "Mint a collision-free trial_id and append the matching pair of lines to trial_strategies (the one-line rule) and trial_strategies_criteria (the metadata + success/failure criteria). Use this for EVERY new trial; never count ids or hand-format the criteria line yourself. Returns {trial_id} (or 'ERROR: ...').",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        episode           = { type = "int", description = "Current episode number." }
                        step_start        = { type = "string",  description = "Step at which the trial activates (as a string), or the literal 'end_of_episode'." }
                        domain            = { type = "string",  description = "One of: rides, shops, staff, research, layout, director, coordinator." }
                        section           = { type = "string",  description = "Target playbook section header (or 'new')." }
                        edit_type         = { type = "string",  description = "'add_line' or 'replace_line'." }
                        new_text          = { type = "string",  description = "The one-line rule to add/replace (no rationale or metrics embedded)." }
                        find_text         = { type = "string",  description = "replace_line only: the exact existing playbook line to replace." }
                        rationale         = { type = "string",  description = "One sentence citing step(s) / metric delta." }
                        success_criterion = { type = "string",  description = "Observable metric + direction + horizon." }
                        failure_criterion = { type = "string",  description = "Observable metric that would falsify the trial." }
                    }
                    required = ["episode", "step_start", "domain", "section", "edit_type", "new_text", "rationale", "success_criterion", "failure_criterion"]
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "ActiveTrials",
            class = "coded_tools.maps_park.active_trials.ActiveTrials",
            function = {
                description = "Return the active trials joined across trial_strategies (rule body) and trial_strategies_criteria (metadata), optionally filtered to one domain. Returns {domain, count, trials:[{trial_id, rule, domain, section, edit_type, find_text, step_start, ep, success_criterion, failure_criterion, rationale}]}.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        domain = { type = "string", description = "Filter to one domain. Omit for all active trials." }
                    }
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "ResolveTrials",
            class = "coded_tools.maps_park.resolve_trials.ResolveTrials",
            function = {
                description = "Apply the curator's per-trial report at episode end: remove confirmed/falsified trials from trial_strategies + trial_strategies_criteria, keep not_applied/inconclusive (and any unreported active trial, as inconclusive note='no_report'), and append an OUTCOME line for every active trial to trial_strategies_outcome. Returns {kept, removed, outcomes_appended}.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        episode = { type = "int", description = "Current episode number." }
                        report  = { type = "string", description = "JSON list of the curator's per-trial objects: [{trial_id, domain, outcome, note}], outcome in confirmed/falsified/not_applied/inconclusive." }
                    }
                    required = ["episode", "report"]
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "PromoteTrial",
            class = "coded_tools.maps_park.promote_trial.PromoteTrial",
            function = {
                description = "Apply ONE confirmed trial's edit to playbook_<domain>.md, tagging the new line '(learned ep<N>)'. add_line appends at end (section 'end'/'new'/empty) or inserts after the named section header; replace_line replaces the unique find_text. On a successful live edit the learned line is also mirrored into the config seed (config_files/<domain>_strategy.md) under a '## Learned rules' section so it survives fresh runs. Returns {action_taken, playbook, line, seed_mirror} where action_taken is promoted / skipped_section_missing / skipped_not_found / skipped_ambiguous / skipped_playbook_missing, and seed_mirror is appended / duplicate_skipped / seed_missing / not_attempted.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        domain    = { type = "string",  description = "rides/shops/staff/research/layout/director/coordinator." }
                        edit_type = { type = "string",  description = "'add_line' or 'replace_line'." }
                        new_text  = { type = "string",  description = "The rule line to add/replace (without the learned tag)." }
                        episode   = { type = "int", description = "Episode number for the '(learned ep<N>)' tag." }
                        section   = { type = "string",  description = "add_line: section header to insert after, or 'end'/'new' to append." }
                        find_text = { type = "string",  description = "replace_line: the exact existing playbook line to replace." }
                    }
                    required = ["domain", "edit_type", "new_text", "episode"]
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "state_read",
            class = "coded_tools.file_management.state_read.StateRead",
            function = {
                description = "Read a file by its logical name from the operator-configured name_map.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        name = { type = "string", description = "Logical name." }
                    },
                    required = ["name"]
                }
            },
            args = {
                name_map = {
                    user_directives             = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/user_directives.md"
                    trial_strategies            = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/trial_strategies.md"
                    trial_strategies_criteria   = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/trial_strategies_criteria.md"
                    trial_strategies_outcome    = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/trial_strategies_outcome.md"
                    last_reward                 = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/last_reward.md"
                    playbook_director           = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_director.md"
                    playbook_coordinator        = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_coordinator.md"
                    playbook_rides              = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_rides.md"
                    playbook_shops              = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_shops.md"
                    playbook_staff              = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_staff.md"
                    playbook_research           = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_research.md"
                    playbook_layout             = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_layout.md"
                    economics_rides             = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/rides_economics.md"
                    economics_shops             = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/shops_economics.md"
                    economics_staff             = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/staff_economics.md"
                    economics_research          = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/research_economics.md"
                    world_constants             = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/world_constants.md"
                    seed_playbook_director      = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/director_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_coordinator   = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/coordinator_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_rides         = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/rides_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_shops         = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/shops_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_staff         = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/staff_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_research      = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/research_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_layout        = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/world_strategy.md"
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "state_write",
            class = "coded_tools.file_management.state_write.StateWrite",
            function = {
                description = "Write content to a state file by logical NAME. mode='overwrite' (default) or 'append'. last_reward is NOT writable here (advance_episode owns it).",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        name    = { type = "string", description = "Logical state name." }
                        content = { type = "string", description = "Text body to write." }
                        mode    = { type = "string", description = "'overwrite' (default) or 'append'." }
                    },
                    required = ["name", "content"]
                }
            },
            args = {
                name_map = {
                    trial_strategies          = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/trial_strategies.md"
                    trial_strategies_outcome  = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/trial_strategies_outcome.md"
                    trial_strategies_criteria = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/trial_strategies_criteria.md"
                    playbook_director         = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_director.md"
                    playbook_coordinator      = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_coordinator.md"
                    playbook_rides            = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_rides.md"
                    playbook_shops            = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_shops.md"
                    playbook_staff            = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_staff.md"
                    playbook_research         = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_research.md"
                    playbook_layout           = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_layout.md"
                }
            }
        }
    ]
}
